%md

### LAB STEP 3: Run prediction on the MNIST data

var outStr = """%html """ for (z <- 0 until dataSamples) { val example = dataSet.getFeatures.getRow(z) val bi = new BufferedImage(28, 28, BufferedImage.TYPE_BYTE_GRAY) for (i <- 0 until (28 * 28)) { bi.getRaster().setSample(i % 28, i / 28, 0, (255 * example.getDouble(i)).toInt) } outStr += "" } outStr += "
imageprediction
" outStr += skilContext.renderBufferedImage(bi) outStr += "" outStr += predictService.classify(new Prediction(example, "example1")).getResults()(0) outStr += "
" println(outStr)
